com.raweng.built

Class BuiltRole

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.raweng.built.BuiltObject
      • com.raweng.built.BuiltRole

  • public class BuiltRole
extends BuiltObject
    To create, modify or delete roles on Built.io Backend server. Roles are a sort of group containing users and other roles. So instead of giving permission to each user, could instead add those users to and assign permissions to the role. All users in the role would inherit permissions that the role receives.
    Author:
    built.io. Inc

      • setUsersWithQuery

        public void setUsersWithQuery(BuiltQuery query)
        To add BuiltQuery instance for users in role


        Note : BuiltQuery instance has to be query on "built_io_application_user" class.

        Parameters:
        query - BuiltQuery instance.

        Example :
         //'blt5d4sample2633b' is a dummy Application API key
 //'blt8h2sample1463j' is a dummy role uid
 BuiltApplication application = Built.application(context, "blt5d4sample2633b");
        
 BuiltRole role = application.role("blt8h2sample1463j");
 BuiltQuery userQuery = application.getUsersQuery();
 userQuery.where("email", "abc@gmail.com");

 role.setUsersWithQuery(userQuery);
